Hardware Wiring Instructions

To build the Smart-Heal Bandage, all components are connected to the ESP32-C3 SuperMini microcontroller.

For the temperature sensing circuit, wire one leg of the NTC thermistor directly to the 3.3V power pin of the ESP32-C3, and connect the other leg to the analog input pin GPIO 0 (A0). To complete the necessary voltage divider for the thermistor, attach a 10kΩ resistor from that exact same GPIO 0 pin and route it to the Ground (GND) pin.

To simulate the analog pH sensor, use a standard 10k potentiometer. 
Connect its left pin to Ground (GND), its right pin to the 3.3V power pin, and wire the middle wiper pin to the analog input pin GPIO 1 (A1).

Next, set up the visual indicators and therapy actuators using three LEDs. 
For the normal healing status, connect the positive (long) leg of the Green LED to digital pin GPIO 3. 
For the infection alert, connect the positive leg of the Red LED to digital pin GPIO 4. 
Finally, for the automated sterilization treatment, connect the positive leg of the Blue LED to digital pin GPIO 5.
To protect the microcontroller, ensure the negative (short) leg of every single LED is connected to Ground (GND) through its own 220Ω current-limiting resistor.
